Gombaleves (Hungarian Mushroom Soup)
  --Girl Cooks World

1 tbsp butter
1 medium onion, finely chopped
1 lb buttom mushrooms
2 tbsp roughly chopped fresh dill + extra for garnish
2 tsp paprika
1/2 tsp smoked paprika (optional)
1 tsp lemon juice
1 c beef, chicken, or vegetable broth
1/2 c milk, at room temp
1/2 c sour cream, at room temp + extra for garnish
1 tbsp cornstarch
2 tbsp water
salt and pepper to taste

In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add onions and cook until they begin to brown. Add the mushrooms, dill, and paprika. Stir well, cover, and cook for ~10 min, stirring occasionally. Add the lemon juice and mix well. Add the broth, cover, and cook for another 10 min. Reduce heat to low. Add milk and stir well. Whisk in the sour cream heat gently until soup is hot. Make a cornstarch slurry with the cornstarch and water, making sure there are no lumps. Add to the soup and stir well. Continue to cook over low heat for a couple of minutes, until the soup has thickened slightly. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve, garnishing with dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of fresh dill, if desired.
